mediaData.Title: Friends
mediaData.Actors: Jennifer Aniston, Courteney Cox, Lisa Kudrow, Matt LeBlanc
mediaData.Plot: Follows the personal and professional lives of six 20 to 30-something-year-old friends living in Manhattan.

mediaData.Title: Vikings
mediaData.Actors: Gustaf Skarsgård, Katheryn Winnick, Alexander Ludwig, Travis Fimmel
mediaData.Plot: The world of the Vikings is brought to life through the journey of Ragnar Lothbrok, the first Viking to emerge from Norse legend and onto the pages of history - a man on the edge of myth.
mediaData.Language: English, Old English, Norse,  Old, Latin

E01.Title: Rites of Passage
E01.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E01.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig
E01.Plot: Ragnar goes on a trip of initiation with his son. Meanwhile, he thinks he has finally found a way to sail ships to the west. However, his beliefs are seen as insane so he chooses to go against the law.

E02.Title: Wrath of the Northmen
E02.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E02.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig
E02.Plot: The stage is set for the first journey west by Ragnar Lothbrok as he gathers a crew willing to risk their lives to travel into the unknown.

E03.Title: Dispossessed
E03.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E03.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig
E03.Plot: A monastery in Lindesfarne, England is about to get a firsthand look at how the Vikings operate.

E04.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E04.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig

E06.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Clive Standen, Katheryn Winnick, Jessalyn Gilsig
E06.Plot: Ragnar, weak and still hurt, must meet the Earl head-on after it comes to light that Rollo has been tortured on Haraldson's orders.

E07.Title: A King's Ransom
E07.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E07.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig
E07.Plot: Three Viking ships sail upriver towards the very heart of power in eastern England: the Royal Villa of King Aelle.

E08.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E08.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig

E09.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig
E09.Plot: At the behest of King Horik, Ragnar assembles a small party to travel to Gotaland (modern day Sweden) to resolve a land dispute with the area's leader, Jarl Borg.

E01.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig

E02.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig, Gustaf Skarsgård

E05.Writer: Michael Hirst (creator), Michael Hirst
E05.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig
E05.Plot: Lagertha and Ragnar unite once again; Aslaug must face the truth of her prophecies; Athelstan struggles to define his faith; Bjorn must once again make a choice.

E06.Actors: Travis Fimmel, Katheryn Winnick, Clive Standen, Jessalyn Gilsig

mediaData.Actors: K.J. Apa, Lili Reinhart, Camila Mendes, Cole Sprouse
mediaData.Plot: A subversive take on Archie and his friends, exploring small town life, the darkness and weirdness bubbling beneath Riverdale's wholesome facade.
